---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { externalLinks } from '../../../config';

const proposalFormHref = 'https://github.com/iso24229/proposals/issues/new?template=system-proposal.yml';
const proposalBrowseHref = 'https://github.com/iso24229/proposals/issues';
---

<Layout title="Apply">
  <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Apply</p>
  <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold tracking-[-0.035em] mb-6">Propose a system.</h1>

  <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-ink-muted max-w-2xl leading-relaxed mb-10">
    Anyone with a GitHub account can propose a new conversion system, a new authority, or a change to an existing entry. Every proposal enters the same lifecycle: submission, Registration Authority review, Advisory Group deliberation, decision.
  </p>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-3 mb-12">
    <a href="/about/apply/submit" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-sm bg-ink text-paper text-sm font-medium hover:bg-ink-muted transition-colors">
      Use the interactive form (recommended)
      <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
    </a>
    <a href={proposalFormHref} class="text-sm text-ink-muted hover:text-gold-deep dark:hover:text-gold-bright underline">
      Or open a raw GitHub issue form
    </a>
  </div>

  {/* ── Lifecycle ───────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="rule-section">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The lifecycle</p>
    <h2 class="max-w-2xl mb-8">From submission to register entry.</h2>

    <ol class="max-w-2xl space-y-8">
      <li class="grid grid-cols-[2rem_1fr] gap-x-4">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-subtle tabular-nums pt-1">01</span>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-lg font-semibold tracking-[-0.012em]">Submission</p>
          <p class="text-ink-muted mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">
            You fill out the <a href="/about/apply/submit" class="underline">interactive form</a> on this site, which validates each field, generates a live code preview, and produces ready-to-paste Markdown with a SHA-256 integrity checksum. The output opens a new issue in <a href={proposalBrowseHref} class="underline"><span class="font-mono">iso24229/proposals</span></a> — a public GitHub repo. (You can also use the <a href={proposalFormHref} class="underline">raw GitHub issue form</a> if you prefer, but you'll lose the validation and checksum.) The form requires identification (your GitHub account), an authority (existing approved, new, or Varia), the four code segments, a defining reference, three independent demonstrative sources, and a justification.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="grid grid-cols-[2rem_1fr] gap-x-4">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-subtle tabular-nums pt-1">02</span>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-lg font-semibold tracking-[-0.012em]">Administrative review (RA, public)</p>
          <p class="text-ink-muted mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">
            The Registration Authority (CalConnect, operated by Ribose) checks completeness, validates codes, and confirms authority authorization within 14 days. Clarifying questions appear as comments on your proposal — you'll be <span class="font-mono">@mentioned</span>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="grid grid-cols-[2rem_1fr] gap-x-4">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-subtle tabular-nums pt-1">03</span>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-lg font-semibold tracking-[-0.012em]">AG deliberation (private)</p>
          <p class="text-ink-muted mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">
            When ready, the proposal is mirrored to <span class="font-mono">iso24229/decisions</span> — a private repo accessible only to Advisory Group members. The AG of 4–12 experts (including an ISO/TC 46 representative) discusses and votes. As a rule, decisions are by consensus; if a vote is needed, more than two-thirds must approve.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="grid grid-cols-[2rem_1fr] gap-x-4">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-subtle tabular-nums pt-1">04</span>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-lg font-semibold tracking-[-0.012em]">Decision (public)</p>
          <p class="text-ink-muted mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">
            The outcome is posted as a comment on your proposal. If approved, an automated workflow generates the YAML and opens a PR to the register; once merged, the entry appears on <a href="/" class="underline">www.iso24229.org</a> with <span class="font-mono">registrationStatus: proposed</span>. If rejected, the proposal is closed; no register entry is created.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="grid grid-cols-[2rem_1fr] gap-x-4">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-subtle tabular-nums pt-1">05</span>
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-lg font-semibold tracking-[-0.012em]">Public review → accepted</p>
          <p class="text-ink-muted mt-1.5 leading-relaxed">
            After a public review period, the AG transitions the entry to <span class="font-mono">registrationStatus: accepted</span> at its next bimonthly meeting. Codes are then reserved indefinitely for backwards compatibility, even if later deprecated.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  {/* ── Three repos ────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="rule-section">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Three repos</p>
    <h2 class="max-w-2xl mb-6">Why three repositories.</h2>
    <p class="text-ink-muted max-w-2xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
      The lifecycle uses three GitHub repositories. This separation keeps public auditability of proposals and outcomes, while protecting AG deliberation from outside pressure.
    </p>
    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="border border-rule rounded p-5">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-subtle mb-2">PUBLIC</p>
        <p class="font-display font-semibold tracking-[-0.012em]">iso24229/proposals</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">Submission queue. Every proposal is a GitHub issue. Public comments for RA clarifications.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-rule rounded p-5 bg-paper-raised">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-subtle mb-2">PRIVATE</p>
        <p class="font-display font-semibold tracking-[-0.012em]">iso24229/decisions</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">AG members only. Discussion, voting, rationale all stay here. Only the outcome is published back.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-rule rounded p-5">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-subtle mb-2">PUBLIC</p>
        <p class="font-display font-semibold tracking-[-0.012em]">iso24229/register</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">The authoritative register. Approved proposals land here as YAML files via automated PRs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ── What you'll need ────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="rule-section">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Before you submit</p>
    <h2 class="max-w-2xl mb-6">What you'll need.</h2>
    <ul class="max-w-2xl space-y-3 text-ink-muted leading-relaxed list-disc pl-6">
      <li><strong class="text-ink">A defining reference</strong> — the authoritative document specifying the system (published romanization table, ISO standard, etc.). Title, publisher, date, URL if available. Drag-and-drop PDF or image excerpts of the relevant pages.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Three independent public sources</strong> demonstrating actual use. Must be independent of both the authority and you. Library catalogues, gazetteers, academic publications, government style guides, software localisation projects.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Authorization</strong> — if proposing for an approved authority, you must be the authority itself or an authorized representative. Otherwise, propose for <span class="font-mono">Var</span> (Varia) or propose a new authority alongside the system.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">A complete system identification</strong> — ISO 639 source language, ISO 15924 source and target scripts, an identifying segment (year or version), a human-readable name, and a one-sentence abstract.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Example conversions</strong> — at least one <span class="font-mono">&lt;input&gt; → &lt;output&gt;</span> pair so the AG can verify the rules are well-defined.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  {/* ── Integrity controls ─────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="rule-section">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Integrity controls</p>
    <h2 class="max-w-2xl mb-6">How the register protects against unauthorized submissions.</h2>
    <p class="text-ink-muted max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
      Three paths, depending on your relationship to the system:
    </p>
    <ul class="max-w-2xl space-y-3 mt-4 text-ink-muted leading-relaxed list-disc pl-6">
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Existing approved authority</strong> — submitter must be the authority itself or have an email/username on file as one of its two authorised persons (per Annex A.4). The RA cross-references this during administrative review.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">New authority</strong> — submitter provides official contact details; the AG verifies the contact before approving.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Varia authority (<span class="font-mono">Var</span>)</strong> — anyone may propose. The AG itself is the de facto authority for these systems (typically historic systems with no clear current owner, e.g. Wade-Giles).</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <p class="mt-12">
    <a href="/about/apply/submit" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-sm bg-ink text-paper text-sm font-medium hover:bg-ink-muted transition-colors">
      Use the interactive form
      <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
    </a>
  </p>
</Layout>
